<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers Wetteland May Start on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORT CHARLOTTE, Fla. (AP) -- Texas Rangers reliever John  
Wetteland may start the season on the disabled list because of a 
string of injuries during spring training. 
</P>
<P>
	Wetteland, slowed by an ankle injury last month and muscle  
spasms in his lower back, was told by manager Johnny Oates not to 
pitch in games for another four days. The All-Star closer is to be 
evaluated on Monday and Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Wetteland made his first spring appearance March 12 and in two  
appearances last week allowed six runs in an inning, lacking 
command of his fastball. 
</P>
<P>
	``The delivery that I saw on Thursday, I didn't like it at  
all,'' Oates said. ``He just can't push off on that ankle well 
enough for me. I'm not sure this is something we can fight through. 
I'm not sure he can pitch that way.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Oates' original plan was for Wetteland to pitch either Saturday  
or Sunday against the Reds, but the back spasms prevented him from 
getting on the mound. 
</P>
<P>
	Wetteland attributed the spasms to overcompensating in his  
delivery because of the injured ankle. He said the ankle soreness 
has been making him depend on upper body strength, putting more 
pressure on his back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
