<HEADLINE>  D.C. United 5, Mutiny 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Roy Lassiter had two goals and Carlos Llamosa  
and Jaime Moreno scored four minutes apart early in the second half 
as D.C. United beat Tampa Bay 5-2 in a Major League Soccer opener 
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Lassiter, traded from Tampa Bay to D.C. United last season, made  
it 3-0 in the 66th minute and added his second goal in the 86th 
minute. He has 20 goals in 26 games with United. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had a real good feeling before the game,'' D.C. United coach  
Thomas Rongen said. ``The core of our players have been together 
and they were ready to play. There was a lot of emotion in he 
lockeroom.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Llamosa's header following a corner kick by Marco Etcheverry in  
the 50th minute made it 1-0 and Moreno made it 2-0 in the 54th 
minute from point-blank range after Ben Olsen's feed. 
</P>
<P>
	Jefferson Gottardi scored Tampa Bay's goals in the 67th and 88th  
minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm disappointed and angry because from my standpoint for what  
I feel our team was capable of, we didn't play,'' Mutiny coach Tim 
Hankinson said. ``On the most exciting day of the year, our guys 
did not give us their fight.'' 
</P>
