<HEADLINE> Sara Lee Meat Plant Being Probed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ZEELAND, Mich. (AP) -- The Sara Lee Corp. meat processing plant  
connected to a deadly outbreak of Listeria bacteria is under 
investigation by a federal grand jury, a company spokeswoman said 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Sara Lee spokeswoman Theresa Herlevsen said the U.S. attorney's  
office in Grand Rapids is investigating Bil Mar Foods in Zeeland. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not something that's unusual in light of the  
circumstances,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Hot dogs and other packaged meat from the Bil Mar plant have  
been linked to 15 deaths, six miscarriages and stillbirths and 
about 100 illnesses in 22 states, according to the federal Centers 
for Disease Control and Prevention. 
</P>
<P>
	Herlevsen said the Chicago-based Sara Lee is cooperating with  
the grand jury and conducting its own investigation. 

</P>
</TEXT>
