<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stars Reacquire Hogue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- The Dallas Stars on Sunday reacquired forward  
Benoit Hogue who left the club as a free agent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Stars obtained the much-traveled Hogue and a conditional  
draft pick in 2001 from the Tampa Bay Lightning in exchange for 
defenseman Sergey Gusev. 
</P>
<P>
	``Benoit will add depth and experience to our group of  
forwards,'' said Stars general manager Bob Gainey. ``He will be a 
valuable addition to our team as we enter the stretch run of the 
season and the playoffs.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hogue, 32, had 11 goals and 14 assists in 62 games this season  
with the Lightning. He was third on the team in goals and points. 
He signed with the Lightning as a free agent last summer after 
playing two-plus seasons with the Stars. 
</P>
<P>
	In 732 career games with the Buffalo Sabres, New York Islanders,  
Toronto Maple Leafs, Stars and Lightning, Hogue has 208 goals and 
293 assists. 
</P>
<P>
	He had six goals and 16 assists in 53 contests with the Stars in  
1997-98. 
</P>
<P>
	Gusev, 23, had one goal with four assists in 22 games with the  
Stars this season. He also has six assists in 11 games with the 
Michigan K-Wings, the Stars' International Hockey League affiliate. 
</P>
<P>
	Hogue was expected to join the division-leading Stars on Monday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
