<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Clouds and rain showers darkened New England on Sunday. Storms  
also developed over the Mid-Atlantic and Southeast, while dry 
weather dominated the Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	A very dry frontal system along with high pressure in the  
Dakotas and in the Texas Panhandle kept locations from the front 
range of the Rockies to the Mississippi River dry. 
</P>
<P>
	An area of low pressure pushing into the Intermountain West  
continued to provide some precipitation to the region. Spotty 
showers and a few thundershowers were scattered across southern 
Wyoming and northeastern Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
	A few clouds were also moving through portions of Washington and  
Southern California, however the clouds were more scattered in 
these areas. The desert Southwest through the southern Rockies were 
under fair skies and dry conditions. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 7 in  
Milan, N.H., to an afternoon high of 81 in Titusville, Fla. With 
the wind chill, it felt like minus 18 in Grand Marais, N.H. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
