<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-21 05:21:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Galaxy 2, Rapids 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Welton, Clint Mathis and Daniel  
Hernandez scored in the shootout to help the Los Angeles Galaxy 
defeat the Colorado Rapids 2-1 Saturday night in the season opener. 
</P>
<P>
	Mathis gave Los Angeles a 1-0 lead in the 14th minute. Welton  
took Joe Franchino's pass and dribbled all the way into the penalty 
area. Peter Vermes then poked the ball away, and it rolled to 
Mathis, who put a 15-yard shot past goalkeeper Marcus Hahnemann. 
</P>
<P>
	Ross Paule tied the score in the 34th minute. Joey DiGiamarino  
sent a cross to Jorge Dely Valdes, who headed it back to Paule, who 
then scored from 12 yards out. 
</P>
<P>
	Hahnemann preserved the tie in the 80th minute by stopping Cobi  
Jones' shot. The rebound went to Mathis, whose header rolled wide 
and out of bounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles took a 2-0 lead in the shootout on goals by Welton  
and Mathis. The Rapids failed to score on their first three shots. 
Goalkeeper Kevin Hartman made a save on Wolde Harris' opening 
shootout shot and shots by DiGiamarino and Vermes went wide. 
</P>
<P>
	David Vaudreuil scored for Colorado on its fourth shot, but  
Hernandez' goal ended the shootout. 
</P>
<P>
	The Galaxy led 13-10 in shots and 6-3 in shots on goal.  
Hahnemann made six saves while Hartman made three. 
</P>
<P>
	Saturday's game was played before a crowd of 17,343 at the Rose  
Bowl, the smallest of the Galaxy's four openers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
